    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>PizzaExpress</strong> <strong>pizza dough</strong> in half</p><p>Shape the <strong>dough</strong> into 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> balls and set aside for 15 min</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pizzaexpress-margherita-pomodoro/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dice the<strong> mozzarella </strong>into small bite-sized pieces and add to some kitchen paper</p><p>Press down on the <strong>diced mozzarella</strong> with another piece of kitchen paper to squeeze out as much liquid as you can</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pizzaexpress-margherita-pomodoro/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> garlic oil</strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>baby plum tomatoes </strong>in half</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pizzaexpress-margherita-pomodoro/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the dough balls have rested for 15 min, press your palm into the middle of a <strong>dough ball</strong> to flatten it until it is twice as wide</p><p>Turn the<strong> dough </strong>over and repeat a few times, until approx. 24cm in diameter (use a <strong>rolling pin</strong> to help you!)</p><p>Repeat with the other <strong>dough ball<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>\u2013 these are your <strong>pizza bases</strong></p><p>Transfer the <strong>pizza bases</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pizzaexpress-margherita-pomodoro/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Spread 4 tbsp <strong>finely chopped tomatoes</strong> over each pizza base (save the rest for another recipe!)</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>halved tomatoes</strong>, <strong>diced mozzarella </strong>and<strong> dried oregano</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>garlic oil</strong> and season with a double pinch of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pizzaexpress-margherita-pomodoro/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 9-19 min or until the pizza bases are golden and crisp and the mozzarella has melted</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? You may have to do this in batches!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pizzaexpress-margherita-pomodoro/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pizzas are ready, top them with <strong>basil leaves</strong></p><p>Drizzle over a little <strong>olive oil</strong> \u2013 these are your <strong>margherita pomodoro pizzas</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pizzaexpress-margherita-pomodoro/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>margherita pomodoro pizza</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
